      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Gannon responded saying, ‚ÄúWe pointed out not just that‚Ä¶ the excessive availability of general jurisdiction could cause international concerns for trade with the United States and our commercial interests, but also the petitioner had called into question the constitutionality of a federal statute, and so we thought that it was important to make sure that the court‚Äôs decision here wouldn‚Äôt implicate the constitutionality of federal statutes.‚Äù",
