            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The federal government said in its amicus brief that Pennsylvania‚Äôs law amounted to an overreach of the state‚Äôs authority. ‚Äú[The law] subverts interstate federalism by reaching beyond Pennsylvania‚Äôs borders and allowing state courts to hear cases in which Pennsylvania has no legitimate interest,‚Äù Justice Department lawyers ",
